2.5 We recommended and Management agreed to implement the following
measures to assure the reliability of balances of PPE accounts:
• Creation of Inventory Committee to undertake the inventory taking;
• Physical inventory of fixed assets shall be made at least once a year;
• Establishment of property identification and coding;
• Maintenance of the Acknowledgement Receipt of Equipment to establish
the official accountable for the property;
• Preparation of inventory reports of PPE;
• Reconciliation of the inventory report with the balances reflected in the
financial statements, identification of persons accountable for loss of
property, and proper adjustment in the financial statements, if any; and
• Maintenance of updated Property Card and Property Plant and
Equipment Ledger Cards.

We recommended the following:
• That the Municipal Accountant exert more effort to trace and identify the variance and reconcile all the records;
• For Management to make representation with the Land Bank of the Philippines for the reconciliation of their individual records and obtain other related loan documents as reference in the adjusting the books to reflect the correct balances of accounts in the Financial Statements;
• That the Municipal Accountant maintain Subsidiary Ledger for individual loan releases regularly reconciled with the General Ledger; and
• For the Municipal Accountant to present properly the current and non-current portion of the Loans Payable – Domestic account in the Financial Statements.

