10.8	In view of the foregoing observations, we have recommended that management:
Justify the above noted lapses;
Require the Municipal Accountant to maintain a special trust fund in the General Fund for the 20% Development Fund to facilitate monitoring of its utilization and ensure that the fund is used for authorized and eligible programs, projects and activities;
Submit the revised Accomplishment Report on the utilization of the 20% Development Fund showing at least the category and details of the projects/activities financed under the fund; and
Adhere strictly with the provisions of Joint Memorandum Circular No. 2017-1 of the DILG and DBM on the appropriation and utilization of the 20% of the IRA for development projects.

